ADOPT-A-BAND PROGRAM CIMS stores have one thing that most chain stores do not: a strong repeat business based on years of trust and service established between each store and its customers. The Adopt-A-Band program allows labels to tap into this bond and help your artist stand out above the rest of the pack. This Adopt-A-Band program is the cornerstone of the Coalition's marketing efforts. All CIMS member stores adopt your artist during a calendar month and give your release the thumbs-up to the customers. Given the number of CD's bought solely based on employee recommendations at CIMS stores, this program is priceless. The Adopt-A-Band program includes: иа а а а Sale pricing and positioning иа а а а Mandatory daily instore play иа а а а Instore play reports to all charts иа а а а Displays at all stores иа а а а Instore signage designating the release as a CIMS-recommended title иа а а а Aggressively monitored compliance иа а а а Artist bio and music samples on the CIMS website (www.cimsmusic.com) иа а а а Wrap-up book upon completion of promotion Again, all this is on a calendar month period. Another unique aspect of this program is that CIMS accounts must vote the release into the program. CIMS has turned down thousands of dollars because members did not feel that the nominated artist would fit well into this program. CIMS member stores have a responsibility to both the label and the customer when they put their good name behind a release. In some cases, it has been more beneficial to all parties that CIMS stores turn down a project that wasn't right, rather than, as many other retailers would, take the money and run. To be considered for the Adopt-A-Band program: labels must submit a copy of the release to the primary contact at each CIMS account. The CIMS office then puts the release up for a vote after the accounts have had some time to listen to the release. After a band is adopted into the program, the label then supplies all the support components available to make an impact at CIMS accounts. COST: $12,000 / title / month <br>
<br>
<br>
 <br>
ONE-STOP SHOPPING FOR ALL YOUR MARKETING AND ADVERTISING The Coalition of Independent Music Stores now handles blanket marketing and advertising efforts for all CIMS stores. This works best with artists that are beyond the developing artist stage, but nevertheless need support at the independent retail level. The CIMS national advertising program also helps you book advertising with all the CIMS accounts in one fell swoop, instead of having to call each account individually. Imagine handling marketing and advertising for all 30 CIMS accounts nationwide at one time: no multiple charge-backs, no having to track down 20 requests from 18 reps in 12 districts, no Swiss-cheese ad planners with holes the size of the Holland Tunnel....just one PO, one check, one-stop shopping for all your CIMS marketing and advertising. Simply call the CIMS HQ (205.879.9023) or contact Don VanCleave (don@cimsmusic.com) and let us know which title you wish to feature. CIMS accounts propose the most effective plan for their markets, and the CIMS office then submits this compiled information to you for approval. Not only do you get targeted strategies from the master of each market, but you also receive lower advertising rates, based on long-term relationships between the stores and their local advertising media! CIMS tacks on a 15% administrative fee to cover the overhead and administrative work, but consider it a drop in the bucket compared to the time and money you save by not having two dozen people nationwide chasing approvals and filling out redundant paperwork. Total program costs vary, depending on the size of your budget.<br>
<br>
<br>
